Node.js Essentials - Stream Write:

- Using streams, write a string "Node.js is an ultimate backend javascript for backend development" into a file named Big_data.txt.
- Write your implementation code in App.js file.
- It is important to use streams while writing the data to the file.

--------------------------------------------------

//write your code here

const fs = require('fs');
const writeData = "Node.js is an ultimate backend javascript for backend development";
const writableStream = fs.createWriteStream("Big_data.txt");
writableStream.write(writeData, 'utf-8');
writableStream.end();
